# 3. Core Operating Principles

---

## Principle 1

Human Kinetic Compression

Pedal force creates mechanical motion.

A portion of that motion drives:

```text
Pedal Stroke
       ↓
Compression Action
       ↓
Pressure Generation
```

---

## Principle 2

Hydraulic Energy Storage

Generated force is stored within hydraulic chambers.

Possible storage mediums:

* Hydraulic fluid
* Elastomeric accumulators
* Pneumatic reservoirs

---

## Principle 3

Pneumatic Buffering

Air chambers smooth pressure fluctuations.

Benefits:

* Reduced shock loading
* Smoother power delivery
* Improved rider comfort

---

## Principle 4

Timed Energy Release

Stored pressure is released only when advantageous.

Examples:

```text
Hill Climb
Acceleration
Cargo Transport
Headwind Compensation
```

---

## Principle 5

Rotational Amplification

Stored energy contributes to wheel rotation through mechanical coupling.

